::: {#def-amenable}

For simplicity, we will use the alternative and equivalent definition that a group, $\AmenableGroup$, is *amenable* (and second countable) if and only if it has a Følner sequence.
:::

::: {#def-density}

For $A\subseteq\Group$ and Følner sequence $\Folner=(\Folner[N])_{n=1}^\infty$, we write
\begin{align*}
    \overline{d}_{\Folner}(A)&=\limsup_{N\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\CountingMeasure{A\cap\Folner[N]}}{\CountingMeasure{\Folner[N]}}
    \\\underline{d}_{\Folner}(A)&=\liminf_{N\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\CountingMeasure{A\cap\Folner[N]}}{\CountingMeasure{\Folner[N]}}
\end{align*}
to be the *upper and lower densities of $A$ with respect to $\Folner$*, respectively. If these agree, then we can write
$$
d_{\Folner}(A)=\lim_{N\rightarrow\infty}\frac{\CountingMeasure{A\cap\Folner[N]}}{\CountingMeasure{\Folner[N]}}
$$
to be the *density of $A$ with respect to $\Phi$*. We also define the *upper Banach density of $A$* by
$$
\overline{d}(A)=\sup\{d_{\Folner}(A):\text{for Følner sequences }\Folner\text{ where }d_{\Folner}(A)\text{ exists}\}.
$$
:::
